- The integer parameter `n` must be greater than or equal to 1.
- The integer 2D array parameter `paths` must not be null.
- The integer 2D array parameter `paths` must have a length less than or equal to 2 times the value of `n`.
- Each subarray in the integer 2D array parameter `paths` must have a length of 2.
- The values in each subarray of the integer 2D array parameter `paths` must be within the range of 1 to `n`.
- The values in each subarray of the integer 2D array parameter `paths` must be distinct.
- Each garden in the integer parameter `n` must have at most 3 paths coming into or leaving it.
- The integer array result `answer` must have a length equal to the value of `n`.
- The integer array result `answer` must contain values denoting the type of flower planted in each garden, which are 1, 2, 3, or 4.
- For any two gardens connected by a path in the integer 2D array parameter `paths`, they must have different types of flowers planted in them.